title: The Freak Show: Tootie's June 2015 Mix
description:
Some things never change. But some things do. Tootie's June 2015 Mix takes his monthly mix theme to a whole new level. It features an assault of 80s music, EDM and hard rock, with some other genres mixed in, because it is a Tootie mix after all.

  Rob Zombie - Demon Speeding
  Rick James - Super Freak
  Pat Benatar - Invincible
  Stevie Nicks - Edge of Seventeen
  Romeo Void - Never Say Never
  Corona - Baby Baby
  Daniel Bedingfield - Gotta Get Thru This
  Denzal Park - Filter Freak
  Tujamo & Jacob Plant - All Night
  Martin Garrix & Jay Hardway - Wizard
  Venal Flesh - Emulgent Disfigurement
  Ajmal - Freak
  The Beatangers - Baby Don't Stop
  h@k - Disco Fantasy
  Eiffel 65 - Brightly Shines
  Linkin Park - Crawling
  Tool - Schism
  Korn - Alone I Break
  Staind - Suffocate
  Slayer - Perversions of Pain
  Static-X - Bled For Days
  3 Doors Down - Loser
  Papa Roach - Scars
  Puddle of Mudd - Never Change
  The National - Exile / Vilify
  Chris Vrenna - Pool of Tears
  Eminem - Role Model

*Contains lossy compression artifacts

All tracks are sourced from lossless material. All of the compilations' songs utilize playback gain values from Tootie's personal volume-leveling procedure, resulting in a consistent overall listening experience without the need to adjust the volume between songs. The method focuses on vocal volume.
